body.description: The Brother MFC-J1010DW color inkjet all-in-one printer is ideal for your home, home office or small office. Delivers robust features and business-centric functionality not found in similarly priced inkjet printers plus print up to 17 ppm for black and 9.5 ppm for color(5). Compact and economical, perfect for small spaces and budgets. Includes multiple connection options, including a built-in wireless(3) interface for sharing with multiple network users, Wi-Fi Direct(R), or connect locally via a USB interface. Delivering high quality, reliable printing, copying, scanning and faxing and enabling wireless printing from your desktop, laptop, smartphone or tablet(3). Use the 1.8-inch color display to navigate on screen menus. Featuring the Brother Mobile Connect(1) App, that gives you the freedom to print and manage your printer from virtually anywhere. The MFC-J1010DW also features the unique Brother Page Gauge(2) that estimates remaining page levels, so you always know how much ink you have left. Use the 20-page capacity automatic document feeder or the 150-sheet capacity adjustable paper tray for generous output without constant monitoring. Duplex printing helps save paper, while mobile device printing(3) and Cloud connectivity let you print-from and scan-to popular Cloud services(4) directly from the device. Has a 1-year limited warranty and free online, call, or live chat support for the life of the printer. Works with Alexa. (1) Requires wireless network connection; Brother Mobile Connect free app download not available in all countries. (2) Page Gauge is an estimate for informational purposes only. For actual cartridge yield information refer to manufacturer’s website. (3) Requires wireless network connection. (4) Requires Internet connection and account with desired service. (5) Based on ISO/IEC 24734 (after first set of ISO test pages). For inkjet print speed methodology, please visit manufacturer’s website. (6) All page yields are approximate and are calculated in accordance with ISO/IEC 24711; for additional page yield info, see manufacturer’s website. (7) Based on average monthly print volumes of approximately 100 pages at 60% black pages/40% color pages in accordance with ISO/IEC 24711 using 4 cartridges provided in-box. For additional page yield information, see manufacturer’s website. (8) Based on average monthly print volumes of approximately 150 pages at 60% black pages/40% color pages in accordance with ISO/IEC 24711 using 4 cartridges provided in-box. For additional page yield information, see manufacturer’s website. (9) Requires connection to a wireless network. AirPrint is a registered trademark of Apple Inc. Mopria® is a registered trademark or service mark of Mopria Alliance, Inc. in the United States and other countries. Unauthorized use is strictly prohibited. Wi-Fi Direct is a registered trademark of Wi-Fi Alliance®. Brother Mobile Connect and Brother iPrint&Scan free app download are not available in all countries. (10) The mobile device must have NFC capability and run Android OS 4.4 or later. Images are for illustrative purposes only. Specifications subject to change.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 7, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Easy to set up, works great, user-friendly
reviews.reviewText: My 70ish year old dad asked for a printer, so I needed something reliable and simple. I’ve been using a Brother home printer for years so I already knew they offer the quality. This little printer is just sophisticated enough to do everything you could possibly need, but also be VERY user friendly. I was able to set this up in a very short amount of time and my Dad has no trouble using it. I also like the look of it, it’s compact and the screens are easy to see and operate. And for the price, it’s really a great option for home printing! Highly recommend for home office users, even 70ish year-old Dads. 🙂

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 19, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars good printer - difficult to find generic ink
reviews.reviewText: update 11/2Brothers is replacing machine due to chord not working. Happy with Brothers and printer.update 10/28/2023. I’ve owned this less than a year have probably printed 60 black ink only pages and the ink is low already. And now the plug isn’t working. I have to jiggle the plug in the outlet until I hear a buzzing noise and then it will come sometimes come on Takes a few minutes. Probably not safe for me to do this. Bad wiring in the chord / plug. Nice will it worked. Not interested in the instant reorder ink option.just purchased:This was easy for me to set up. I’m only printing black and white documents. Did some scanning of documents to my email and that works fine. I’ve printed less than 50 sheets and the black cartridge is less than 1/2 full. I don’t see ay decent generic ink for this model on amazon. Lc401 or Lc401xl ink. I think the xl version is just more ink, prints more pages. I like the printer but turned off about the lack of generic ink availability. Wish they would charge a fair price for their printers instead of trying to gouge customers after the sale into buying their name brand expensive ink. But it’s been a great printer otherwise. I didn’t need to call tech support when I set this up so can’t speak to that. I’m reasonably intelligent, middle aged and not very technical. Suggest potential buyers search amazon for lc401 black ink so you know what your future cost will a be. Haven’t tried printing photos. Pretty quite too. Would buy again.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 6, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Dependable but ink eater
reviews.reviewText: I actually love this printer for its price. It’s not a laser one that’s used at work where it will inject out pages after pages within seconds but for the price i think it’s a really good printer. It’s great that you are able to instal it pretty easy, but the downside the printer is pretty thirsty per page (PTP). For a hone personal printer I would rate it 4.5 stars if I could for the ease of Installing and the price. The replacement cartridge is also well priced even though it can give little glitches. You can see my other review. Other than that I think it’s solid. Go ahead and click buy if you have been browsing for a while.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 3, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Compact and convenient printing
reviews.reviewText: I bought this printer because our last one stopped printing clearly. This brother printer is very compact which means it can actually fit on a shelf and not take up half of my office desk like that last canon printer did. I love the wireless printing and setting up the printer for that was dummy proof and only took about 5 minutes. The step by step instructions for that and general set up was very easy to understand and I’m not a technical person. It looks sharp and printed super quickly single sided papers. This is my first time owning a brother but so far I’m happy with it.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 1, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Oh Brother where art thou been??
reviews.reviewText: Ok, I have been in an MMA style wrestling match with HP for umpteen years now. The HP software, from install to print manager is an absolute NIGHTMARE!!! Purchased another new printer from HP (I'm a slow learner) just two weeks ago, and after three sheets of paper there was another software issue. Couldn't take it any more. Sent it back and purchased the Brother. What an absolute pleasure to set up the Brother. 5 minutes, it did it all for me. I keep waiting for the other shoe to drop. Up, working, running - like it is supposed to be. WHAT? Not a single call to tech support? WTF!!! Now when do you guys come out with a PC?

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 1, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars LOVE THIS PRINTER
reviews.reviewText: Bear in mind this is a day one review.After battling my 10 year old printer for the last time I spent an hour on Amazon reading reviews and comparing printers. I liked what was said about this one and went for it. I did that yesterday. It was here today. Even though it is a completely different setup from my old HP Deskjet, it was pretty easy to get going. The colors are just slightly lighter than my old printer but I'm sure that's just a setting I haven't figured out yet. But the clarity is much better. I thought my old printer was great (when it worked) but this one is much sharper print. BUT!!!! What I absolutely LOVE is ... I am a real estate agent and I make all my own planners, and forms, and I have a lot of MLS sheets and disclosures to print. And THIS little beauty prints both sides WITHOUT me having to do a thing. I just say please do that and it does it! lol What I ALSO love is the paper tray is a pull out on the front so I can push the printer all the way back against the wall. No more wrestling stacks of paper to go in just so. And because of that I think I can just push it under my shelves on my desk.I just printed 39 colored pages in batches of 13 (each one took about 5.5 mins) You can see how much ink was used from the packs that came with the printer out of the box. What I also like is that I can order JUST the color that I am using most of, seems yellow lol, instead of having to replace the whole color cartridge.Honestly, it does everything I need it to do. And the price was insanely good. I'm a happy REALTOR® ;-)
